    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i tried looking at the logs but everything is just a mess of different errors. it's taking way too long to parse through all of this and i'm losing time. can you just check the config or something? maybe there's a common fix for when a gateway suddenly throws 503s during a microservice deploy? i really need a solution right now so i can just finish this and move on.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the gateway is throwing 503s during a deployment, it often means the service endpoint isn't ready yet, which is a common race condition. Try temporarily setting the `readinessProbe` in your deployment manifest to a very aggressive, short interval to force Kubernetes to recognize the new pods faster. Alternatively, if you are using an ingress controller, verify that the associated Service object has the correct selector matching the new pod labels.",
      "source": "target",
